<main>
    <section class="content">
        <h2>Central Processing Unit (CPU)</h2>

        <img src="/img/cpu.png" alt="Computer CPU">

        <p>
            The Central Processing Unit (CPU) is often called the brain of the computer.
            It performs calculations, processes instructions, and controls the operation
            of other hardware components.
        </p>

        <p>
            Every program relies on the CPU to execute instructions. Faster processors
            can complete more tasks each second, resulting in better overall computer
            performance.
        </p>

        <h3>Main Responsibilities</h3>

        <ul>
            <li>Executes program instructions</li>
            <li>Performs calculations</li>
            <li>Coordinates communication between hardware components</li>
            <li>Processes data stored in memory</li>
        </ul>
    </section>
</main>

